1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:13,411 --> 00:01:16,122
THREE YEARS AGO

3
00:01:16,206 --> 00:01:18,750
I mean, this is our honeymoon.

4
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:21,878
Why did you want to visit
a cemetery of all places?

5
00:01:21,961 --> 00:01:23,254
You're really something.

6
00:01:25,048 --> 00:01:28,093
I like how there's a cemetery
in the middle of a park.

7
00:01:28,802 --> 00:01:32,013
You're not buried
in a mountain or scattered at sea.

8
00:01:32,639 --> 00:01:34,599
You're resting near your home.

9
00:01:34,682 --> 00:01:36,643
It makes death seem like nothing.

10
00:01:39,979 --> 00:01:40,897
Perhaps.

11
00:01:53,910 --> 00:01:55,286
Is it his wife's grave?

12
00:01:55,370 --> 00:01:57,622
What? What do you mean?

13
00:01:58,706 --> 00:02:00,083
The old man over there.

14
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:01,334
I don't see anyone.

15
00:02:03,962 --> 00:02:05,296
He was just there.

16
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,174
Don't scare me like that.

17
00:02:08,925 --> 00:02:10,260
You know

18
00:02:10,343 --> 00:02:12,303
those husbands in movies

19
00:02:12,387 --> 00:02:15,765
who bring their late wives
flowers every day.

20
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:17,725
He looked like one.

21
00:02:22,147 --> 00:02:23,064
Keep this in mind.

22
00:02:24,274 --> 00:02:26,901
I won't do anything like that for you.

23
00:02:28,903 --> 00:02:29,737
You won't?

24
00:02:29,821 --> 00:02:31,573
If you die before I do,

25
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:34,617
I'm going to live one more day

26
00:02:35,201 --> 00:02:36,619
and then follow you.

27
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:39,998
Whatever.

28
00:02:40,081 --> 00:02:41,541
It's true.

29
00:02:41,624 --> 00:02:43,626
How will I ever live without you?

30
00:02:44,878 --> 00:02:45,712
Whatever.

31
00:02:46,588 --> 00:02:48,089
I mean it.

32
00:02:48,173 --> 00:02:49,549
That's enough.

33
00:02:50,675 --> 00:02:54,012
We put emphasis on our happy moments.

34
00:02:54,095 --> 00:02:56,598
But we don't know

35
00:02:56,681 --> 00:02:58,224
what the future holds for us.

36
00:02:59,225 --> 00:03:02,228
So we make promises we can't keep

37
00:03:02,312 --> 00:03:05,607
and laugh as if
these happy moments will last forever.

38
00:03:05,690 --> 00:03:09,777
However, there is a dark side
behind those radiant moments.

39
00:03:10,904 --> 00:03:13,740
When the magical moments disappeared

40
00:03:13,823 --> 00:03:17,368
and hardships made me want to give up,

41
00:03:18,328 --> 00:03:19,746
a thought crossed my mind.

42
00:03:21,831 --> 00:03:27,045
"Sure. I've experienced many misfortunes,
but I still have you."

43
00:03:28,254 --> 00:03:30,048
And that helped me endure.

44
00:03:43,895 --> 00:03:44,896
However,

45
00:03:45,730 --> 00:03:49,108
I had to make a brutal decision.

46
00:03:55,698 --> 00:03:56,532
So…

47
00:03:58,451 --> 00:03:59,535
you're telling me

48
00:04:01,663 --> 00:04:02,997
to make a decision?

49
00:04:04,457 --> 00:04:06,167
I'll lose my memory if I get it

50
00:04:06,251 --> 00:04:07,627
and die if I don't.

51
00:04:08,503 --> 00:04:10,672
Are you telling me
to pick the lesser evil?

52
00:04:13,383 --> 00:04:15,176
-No.
-Then what?

53
00:04:18,388 --> 00:04:19,222
Forget it.

54
00:04:20,014 --> 00:04:21,140
I'll pretend like…

55
00:04:22,976 --> 00:04:24,310
this was all a good dream.

56
00:04:39,826 --> 00:04:41,703
Let me go. I said, let go.

57
00:04:43,538 --> 00:04:44,455
Don't make a choice.

58
00:04:45,373 --> 00:04:46,582
Don't think.

59
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:49,127
Just listen to me.

60
00:04:50,461 --> 00:04:53,006
Just… live.

61
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:56,926
Do that.

62
00:04:58,886 --> 00:05:00,054
Please…

63
00:05:01,097 --> 00:05:02,140
live.

64
00:05:03,808 --> 00:05:04,642
Okay?

65
00:05:09,605 --> 00:05:10,440
Hae-in.

66
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:13,234
Please live.

67
00:05:16,362 --> 00:05:19,282
At that moment, we had no idea

68
00:05:22,327 --> 00:05:25,246
what was waiting for us on the other side.

69
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,126
EPISODE 14

70
00:05:50,146 --> 00:05:51,898
-Where are you going?
-To see Hae-in.

71
00:05:51,981 --> 00:05:54,233
-She's in Germany for the surgery.
-That's why.

72
00:05:54,317 --> 00:05:57,236
Hyun-woo is there with her,
so why would you go?

73
00:05:59,197 --> 00:06:00,531
I have my own duties to fulfill.

74
00:06:00,615 --> 00:06:03,534
Your duties
and what you must protect lie here.

75
00:06:03,618 --> 00:06:06,329
Why are you obsessing
over a girl who's dying?

76
00:06:07,663 --> 00:06:08,664
She's not dying.

77
00:06:09,415 --> 00:06:12,418
The surgery will save her,
and she'll forget all the bad memories.

78
00:06:12,502 --> 00:06:13,711
She'll start anew.

79
00:06:13,795 --> 00:06:15,797
Do you think she'll give you a chance?

80
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:16,714
Do you disagree?

81
00:06:22,762 --> 00:06:25,515
Beom-seok is getting ready
to take your spot.

82
00:06:25,598 --> 00:06:28,559
Beom-jun has met directors
who favor him since returning.

83
00:06:28,643 --> 00:06:30,144
The stockholders' meeting is soon.

84
00:06:30,228 --> 00:06:32,522
You're going to ruin this all
just for Hae-in?

85
00:06:33,189 --> 00:06:34,732
What's wrong with you?

86
00:06:37,235 --> 00:06:38,653
You shouldn't have left me.

87
00:06:40,071 --> 00:06:41,864
It's all because you abandoned me.

88
00:06:43,157 --> 00:06:46,661
I wouldn't have been curious
about how great this family was

89
00:06:46,744 --> 00:06:48,788
for you to abandon your own son

90
00:06:48,871 --> 00:06:51,124
or have been jealous of Hae-in
and eventually…

91
00:06:52,917 --> 00:06:53,918
fall in love with her.

92
00:06:55,378 --> 00:06:56,921
What will it take for you to stop?

93
00:07:04,011 --> 00:07:05,012
I can't stop.

94
00:07:07,682 --> 00:07:08,850
Not until I die.

95
00:07:17,316 --> 00:07:18,317
Fine.

96
00:07:20,945 --> 00:07:22,447
Then let me help you.

97
00:07:35,376 --> 00:07:36,752
Are you going to Frankfurt?

98
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:38,921
Yes.

99
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:46,846
BODY FOUND NEAR SAMBANG RESERVOIR
IDENTIFIED AS PYEON

100
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:14,392
How did you find me?

101
00:09:15,268 --> 00:09:17,436
You go out every morning,
so I followed you.

102
00:09:17,979 --> 00:09:20,565
At least you're trying hard.

103
00:09:21,315 --> 00:09:22,942
For what?

104
00:09:23,025 --> 00:09:26,112
You need to pray a lot
if you want to go to Heaven.

105
00:09:27,238 --> 00:09:29,782
That way, we'll even meet

106
00:09:30,866 --> 00:09:31,951
in the afterlife.

107
00:09:32,034 --> 00:09:34,495
Is it a given that you'll go to Heaven?

108
00:09:35,246 --> 00:09:36,706
Isn't that obvious?

109
00:09:39,917 --> 00:09:42,044
I wasn't praying so I'd go to Heaven.

110
00:09:44,463 --> 00:09:45,464
Then?

111
00:09:45,965 --> 00:09:48,175
I prayed that you'd get the surgery.

112
00:09:49,176 --> 00:09:52,013
I told God I wouldn't ask
that you remember everything.

113
00:09:54,890 --> 00:09:56,392
I just prayed that you'd live.

114
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,277
What a useless prayer.

115
00:10:07,236 --> 00:10:08,195
Let's go.

116
00:10:16,162 --> 00:10:17,538
Should we write one too?

117
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,335
You'll write something useless.

118
00:10:23,044 --> 00:10:23,878
Let's just go.

119
00:10:38,184 --> 00:10:40,144
I've given you enough time to think.

120
00:10:40,978 --> 00:10:42,772
We can't push it back any longer.

121
00:10:42,855 --> 00:10:45,107
I booked an appointment,
so let's go after breakfast.

122
00:10:45,191 --> 00:10:46,192
We need to go somewhere.

123
00:10:48,611 --> 00:10:49,654
Where?

124
00:11:07,797 --> 00:11:08,964
Recognize this place?

125
00:11:09,674 --> 00:11:11,759
We came on our honeymoon.

126
00:11:11,842 --> 00:11:13,010
We did.

127
00:11:13,094 --> 00:11:15,429
You said it was pretty
and took tons of photos.

128
00:11:15,513 --> 00:11:17,139
There was a pub nearby too.

129
00:11:17,223 --> 00:11:19,225
We had beer and argued.

130
00:11:20,017 --> 00:11:23,604
We did. You said
I was too cute when I got drunk

131
00:11:23,688 --> 00:11:25,147
and told me not to act cute.

132
00:11:26,273 --> 00:11:27,108
No.

133
00:11:27,775 --> 00:11:29,485
I remember vividly.

134
00:11:29,568 --> 00:11:32,279
I told you only to be cute in front of me,

135
00:11:33,364 --> 00:11:35,491
but all the girls were staring at you.

136
00:11:35,574 --> 00:11:38,661
I didn't know that. Why?
Because my eyes were only on you.

137
00:11:41,372 --> 00:11:42,373
Is that so?

138
00:11:43,332 --> 00:11:45,710
You said that then,
and I wasn't mad anymore.

139
00:11:46,711 --> 00:11:47,545
Not right away.

140
00:11:48,838 --> 00:11:50,506
You sulked for about two hours.

141
00:11:50,589 --> 00:11:51,674
Anyway…

142
00:11:52,925 --> 00:11:55,803
We passed this place
on our way back to the hotel

143
00:11:57,179 --> 00:11:59,932
and saw a beautiful full moon.

144
00:12:01,475 --> 00:12:05,062
You're right. It was big and gorgeous.

145
00:12:05,688 --> 00:12:07,606
I still have the photo.

146
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:09,483
I still remember the smell,

147
00:12:10,609 --> 00:12:12,153
the moon, and the wind

148
00:12:14,071 --> 00:12:14,905
of that day.

149
00:12:16,907 --> 00:12:18,492
That's what memories are.

150
00:12:19,869 --> 00:12:21,287
Being alive means

151
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:24,248
I cherish those memories
and draw strength from them.

152
00:12:24,331 --> 00:12:26,375
So those memories define me

153
00:12:27,251 --> 00:12:28,169
and my life.

154
00:12:29,587 --> 00:12:31,422
And I'll be losing them.

155
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:36,677
This place will just become
an ordinary field for me.

156
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:38,554
And you…

157
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,685
will become a stranger.

158
00:12:46,812 --> 00:12:48,063
I'll no longer be myself.

159
00:12:50,941 --> 00:12:53,944
That's why I'm not getting the surgery.

160
00:12:54,779 --> 00:12:56,363
I've lived as myself,

161
00:12:58,365 --> 00:12:59,492
and I'll die as such.

162
00:13:38,405 --> 00:13:41,742
Gosh, Beom-ja. Are you insane?

163
00:13:41,826 --> 00:13:42,868
What are you doing?

164
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:47,832
Where are you going? Back to Yongdu-ri?

165
00:13:47,915 --> 00:13:50,334
Snap out of it. Go back home.

166
00:13:58,092 --> 00:14:00,970
Hey, this is so wrong.

167
00:14:01,762 --> 00:14:03,389
Let's just go shopping.

168
00:14:04,223 --> 00:14:06,350
Let's go to a department store. Hi, Bixby.

169
00:14:06,934 --> 00:14:08,435
-I'm listening.
-Yongdu-ri.

170
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:10,020
I've gone insane.

171
00:14:10,104 --> 00:14:11,313
I actually came back.

172
00:14:11,397 --> 00:14:12,481
Is this your home?

173
00:14:12,565 --> 00:14:15,651
I should've slashed my tires.

174
00:14:19,738 --> 00:14:20,906
Gosh, you idiot!

175
00:14:22,408 --> 00:14:24,243
-You startled me!
-What are you doing here?

176
00:14:25,452 --> 00:14:26,287
I know

177
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:29,540
you like walnut cakes.

178
00:14:30,082 --> 00:14:31,584
-Do I?
-Yes.

179
00:14:31,667 --> 00:14:34,086
-I brought some for you.
-I see.

180
00:14:34,169 --> 00:14:35,254
But why are you here?

181
00:14:35,337 --> 00:14:36,422
This is Yeong-song's house.

182
00:14:36,505 --> 00:14:37,715
Really?

183
00:14:38,549 --> 00:14:40,009
I got the wrong address.

184
00:14:41,051 --> 00:14:42,303
Beom-ja.

185
00:14:42,970 --> 00:14:44,221
What…

186
00:14:51,687 --> 00:14:53,731
-Why--
-She came to see me.

187
00:14:53,814 --> 00:14:55,608
She dotes on me.

188
00:14:57,151 --> 00:14:59,153
Would you like to have some tea?

189
00:14:59,737 --> 00:15:01,113
We have tasty plum tea.

190
00:15:01,739 --> 00:15:02,698
-Should I--
-It's okay.

191
00:15:03,657 --> 00:15:06,744
She came to see me.
She got the wrong address.

192
00:15:06,827 --> 00:15:09,622
I'll see you around. Let's go. It's cold.

193
00:15:10,623 --> 00:15:12,750
-All right.
-Still.

194
00:15:13,334 --> 00:15:16,170
Have some tea
even if you didn't come here for me.

195
00:15:26,347 --> 00:15:28,766
Have some madeleines too.
I just baked them.

196
00:15:28,849 --> 00:15:30,142
Goodness.

197
00:15:31,018 --> 00:15:32,811
Yeong-song.

198
00:15:32,895 --> 00:15:35,481
Your view of life is so modern.

199
00:15:35,564 --> 00:15:38,400
You only work the bare minimum?

200
00:15:38,484 --> 00:15:40,986
We don't need much to live
as we think we do.

201
00:15:41,070 --> 00:15:43,614
-What else do you do then?
-I read and listen to music.

202
00:15:45,574 --> 00:15:46,408
I think I found it.

203
00:15:46,492 --> 00:15:48,577
I always felt stifled
and wanted to run away

204
00:15:48,661 --> 00:15:50,162
when I lived in Seoul.

205
00:15:50,245 --> 00:15:52,456
I'll stay here with Da-hye and Geon-u.

206
00:15:52,539 --> 00:15:54,083
I'm going to work little

207
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:55,876
-and be very happy.
-You?

208
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:58,087
-As if.
-It'll be hard for you.

209
00:15:58,170 --> 00:16:00,714
She's extremely materialistic unlike me.

210
00:16:00,798 --> 00:16:03,467
Hey, I'm not.

211
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,385
You're wrong.

212
00:16:04,468 --> 00:16:06,804
She only carries handbags
worth tens of millions.

213
00:16:06,887 --> 00:16:08,931
One ring costs the same
as an entire apartment.

214
00:16:09,014 --> 00:16:10,057
Do such rings exist?

215
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:12,309
And that's not all.

216
00:16:12,393 --> 00:16:14,061
How much was that watch again?

217
00:16:14,144 --> 00:16:15,312
-Two hundred million?
-Hey!

218
00:16:19,191 --> 00:16:21,485
I'm enjoying this too.

219
00:16:21,568 --> 00:16:23,696
I like having homemade plum tea,

220
00:16:23,779 --> 00:16:27,616
madeleines, and reading and listening
to music without a worry in the world.

221
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,534
I see.

222
00:16:32,538 --> 00:16:34,039
Yes, what is it?

223
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:37,376
All right. Bye.

224
00:16:39,378 --> 00:16:40,337
Mom and Dad are here.

225
00:16:40,421 --> 00:16:42,840
Why do they keep coming?
Da-hye will feel uncomfortable.

226
00:16:42,923 --> 00:16:44,133
I'll call you later.

227
00:16:44,216 --> 00:16:46,301
-Okay.
-Let's go, Aunt Beom-ja!

228
00:16:46,385 --> 00:16:48,137
-I should get going then.
-Okay.

229
00:16:51,473 --> 00:16:52,307
Come by again.

230
00:17:13,662 --> 00:17:16,373
Come again. I'll bake more madeleines.

231
00:17:56,663 --> 00:17:58,457
I wanted to go back to the hotel.

232
00:18:00,292 --> 00:18:02,002
The professor is waiting.

233
00:18:03,629 --> 00:18:05,547
You should at least talk to him.

234
00:18:07,549 --> 00:18:09,343
Your parents are waiting too.

235
00:18:11,553 --> 00:18:13,514
They want to do a video call.

236
00:18:22,231 --> 00:18:25,818
-Where's Da-hye?
-She went out with Geon-u for a stroll.

237
00:18:25,901 --> 00:18:26,944
It's cold out.

238
00:18:27,027 --> 00:18:29,154
I think she was uncomfortable
to see my parents.

239
00:18:29,238 --> 00:18:31,073
Hey, are you not going to greet us?

240
00:18:33,951 --> 00:18:35,744
What's this about?

241
00:18:35,828 --> 00:18:37,746
Hae-in is refusing to get the surgery.

242
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:38,831
What?

243
00:18:39,623 --> 00:18:40,582
She's refusing?

244
00:18:43,085 --> 00:18:45,420
How about we tug at her heartstrings?

245
00:18:45,504 --> 00:18:46,922
-Her heartstrings?
-Let's beg.

246
00:18:47,005 --> 00:18:49,258
"If you die, I'll die."

247
00:18:50,968 --> 00:18:54,221
You don't know her well.
She'll say, "Do as you please."

248
00:18:54,304 --> 00:18:55,722
No way.

249
00:18:55,806 --> 00:18:59,226
She'll know that we're bluffing.
Threatening her won't work.

250
00:18:59,309 --> 00:19:02,020
She's smart since she takes after me.

251
00:19:02,771 --> 00:19:05,440
Then how about we take a logical approach?

252
00:19:05,524 --> 00:19:06,358
How?

253
00:19:06,441 --> 00:19:11,572
There are times when harvesting pears
becomes difficult due to severe blight

254
00:19:11,655 --> 00:19:13,448
even if we use expensive pesticides.

255
00:19:13,532 --> 00:19:16,410
But their roots will rot
if we don't spray them at all.

256
00:19:16,493 --> 00:19:18,412
-You're at a crossroads.
-Exactly.

257
00:19:18,495 --> 00:19:21,707
Even though we anticipate a huge loss,
we choose to spray them anyway

258
00:19:21,790 --> 00:19:24,501
since we need to save the roots

259
00:19:24,585 --> 00:19:25,836
for the upcoming year.

260
00:19:25,919 --> 00:19:30,257
So you choose to save them
despite suffering a loss. I like that.

261
00:19:31,091 --> 00:19:33,051
Then let's do this.

262
00:19:33,135 --> 00:19:34,761
First, we'll try to be logical.

263
00:19:34,845 --> 00:19:38,265
If we fail, you'll step up and scold her.

264
00:19:38,348 --> 00:19:40,517
"Take care of the body
your parents gave you."

265
00:19:40,601 --> 00:19:43,145
"I may not have given birth to you,
but I'm still your father."

266
00:19:43,228 --> 00:19:46,356
Then you can support him and say,
"Let's just all die together."

267
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,942
And then… Okay.

268
00:19:54,114 --> 00:19:56,074
-Hae-in.
-Yes, Mother.

269
00:19:58,577 --> 00:19:59,494
Ma'am, the pear story.

270
00:19:59,578 --> 00:20:01,163
The pears. Pesticides.

271
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:06,668
Goodness.

272
00:20:06,752 --> 00:20:10,297
I have a runny nose. You can go first.

273
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:11,673
Then I'll take over.

274
00:20:11,757 --> 00:20:13,634
Hae-in, you should

275
00:20:13,717 --> 00:20:15,052
think this through.

276
00:20:15,135 --> 00:20:16,720
This will benefit you.

277
00:20:16,803 --> 00:20:20,933
You'll lose your good memories,
but the bad ones too.

278
00:20:21,016 --> 00:20:22,100
Why do you think I drink?

279
00:20:22,184 --> 00:20:25,854
I drown myself in alcohol
to forget the painful memories.

280
00:20:25,938 --> 00:20:27,814
But they keep coming back.

281
00:20:27,898 --> 00:20:31,485
So wouldn't it be a good thing
to forget them forever?

282
00:20:31,568 --> 00:20:34,529
You're not persuading her.

283
00:20:38,784 --> 00:20:39,785
Hae-in.

284
00:20:41,119 --> 00:20:42,287
You must've been shocked.

285
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:45,707
Don't get mad at Hyun-woo.
I told him to keep it from you.

286
00:20:46,792 --> 00:20:48,252
I'm sorry we didn't tell you.

287
00:20:49,253 --> 00:20:51,171
We were afraid you'd refuse to go.

288
00:20:52,339 --> 00:20:53,507
It's okay.

289
00:20:54,091 --> 00:20:55,592
I would've done the same.

290
00:20:55,676 --> 00:20:57,552
After learning about your illness,

291
00:20:57,636 --> 00:21:00,973
I reached out
to hospitals around the world.

292
00:21:01,056 --> 00:21:06,103
And they all said the same thing.
They were already in touch with Hyun-woo.

293
00:21:07,396 --> 00:21:08,230
He had sent

294
00:21:09,189 --> 00:21:11,441
hundreds of emails

295
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:15,946
and called the U.S. and European hospitals
in the middle of the night

296
00:21:16,029 --> 00:21:19,199
to find labs or hospitals
that could save you.

297
00:21:27,082 --> 00:21:30,377
That's how he found that hospital.

298
00:21:31,503 --> 00:21:32,963
So, Hae-in,

299
00:21:33,797 --> 00:21:35,924
please think this through and…

300
00:21:37,009 --> 00:21:40,220
Think? She should focus on living first.

301
00:21:40,304 --> 00:21:41,388
Don't you agree?

302
00:21:41,972 --> 00:21:45,267
Your memories won't matter
if you die, right?

303
00:21:46,184 --> 00:21:47,185
At least…

304
00:21:49,146 --> 00:21:52,232
you'll remember me as a daughter
who had a good relationship

305
00:21:53,859 --> 00:21:55,193
with you.

306
00:21:55,861 --> 00:21:57,738
But after the surgery,

307
00:21:58,697 --> 00:22:00,699
I might turn into a stranger.

308
00:22:02,993 --> 00:22:06,038
The Hae-in who used to argue
so much with you

309
00:22:07,831 --> 00:22:11,209
before tearfully reconciling
will be gone.

310
00:22:12,085 --> 00:22:13,920
I won't recognize you anymore.

311
00:22:22,429 --> 00:22:23,555
Please understand.

312
00:22:23,638 --> 00:22:24,765
I'm sorry.

313
00:22:27,851 --> 00:22:29,936
Okay. Let's hang up.

314
00:22:31,897 --> 00:22:34,566
Rest up, and we'll talk again soon. Okay?

315
00:22:35,609 --> 00:22:37,778
-Wait--
-Why did you turn it off?

316
00:22:37,861 --> 00:22:39,571
She didn't give us an answer yet.

317
00:22:39,654 --> 00:22:42,657
Will you take responsibility
if she refuses the surgery?

318
00:22:42,741 --> 00:22:44,451
Gosh, did you really turn it off?

319
00:22:44,534 --> 00:22:46,036
I wanted to talk to her too.

320
00:22:46,119 --> 00:22:47,954
Why would you?

321
00:22:48,038 --> 00:22:50,665
She already has a lot on her mind.

322
00:22:54,336 --> 00:22:55,712
Are you crying, Dad?

323
00:22:56,713 --> 00:22:57,964
He's crying.

324
00:22:59,132 --> 00:23:02,844
You're making me cry now.

325
00:23:04,137 --> 00:23:05,222
Goodness.

326
00:23:06,556 --> 00:23:07,891
Everyone is crying.

327
00:23:12,229 --> 00:23:15,649
Call her back and persuade her.

328
00:23:16,483 --> 00:23:18,026
What can I say?

329
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:19,403
We should do something.

330
00:23:44,344 --> 00:23:45,512
Geon-u.

331
00:23:45,595 --> 00:23:48,223
Let's go around one more time.

332
00:24:00,735 --> 00:24:02,028
What brings you here?

333
00:24:02,112 --> 00:24:03,989
Shouldn't you apologize first?

334
00:24:05,907 --> 00:24:07,868
-I guess you're not sorry.
-Not to you.

335
00:24:08,910 --> 00:24:10,078
But I'm sorry to my family.

336
00:24:10,162 --> 00:24:11,163
Your family?

337
00:24:12,664 --> 00:24:14,749
You're totally mistaken.

338
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:15,667
Da-hye.

339
00:24:16,334 --> 00:24:17,377
Don't try to change.

340
00:24:17,461 --> 00:24:19,171
But I want to.

341
00:24:20,088 --> 00:24:21,882
No, do what you've always done

342
00:24:21,965 --> 00:24:23,508
and scam those around you.

343
00:24:23,592 --> 00:24:25,302
If not, that so-called family of yours

344
00:24:25,385 --> 00:24:27,179
-will get hurt.
-What do you mean?

345
00:24:27,262 --> 00:24:29,806
Stay here if you're curious.

346
00:24:29,890 --> 00:24:32,434
I came to warn you
since I respect the history

347
00:24:32,517 --> 00:24:33,560
we've shared together.

348
00:24:33,643 --> 00:24:34,644
But…

349
00:24:35,562 --> 00:24:36,980
I can't give you much time.

350
00:24:37,063 --> 00:24:39,858
Give me the USB that you took from Jun-ho

351
00:24:39,941 --> 00:24:42,694
and leave with your son.

352
00:24:45,864 --> 00:24:47,491
You shouldn't have come here.

353
00:24:47,574 --> 00:24:49,451
You should've just stayed in the U.S.

354
00:24:49,534 --> 00:24:50,702
I get what you're saying,

355
00:24:50,785 --> 00:24:53,705
so don't you dare harm Soo-cheol
or my family.

356
00:24:53,788 --> 00:24:55,749
I won't sit still if you do.

357
00:24:55,832 --> 00:24:56,958
What'll you do?

358
00:24:57,918 --> 00:25:01,004
I'll give the USB
to the police or the prosecution.

359
00:25:01,087 --> 00:25:02,297
Let's go down together.

360
00:25:02,380 --> 00:25:04,257
You shouldn't say that as a mom.

361
00:25:04,341 --> 00:25:05,800
Who'll look after Geon-u?

362
00:25:05,884 --> 00:25:08,386
Will this family
take care of a kid who's not theirs?

363
00:25:09,679 --> 00:25:10,680
Hey!

364
00:25:12,015 --> 00:25:14,476
Why are you out in the cold?

365
00:25:14,559 --> 00:25:16,728
Geon-u might catch a cold.

366
00:25:16,811 --> 00:25:17,812
Seon-hwa.

367
00:25:18,730 --> 00:25:21,983
Do you even know who Da-hye really is?

368
00:25:24,986 --> 00:25:26,613
It doesn't matter.

369
00:25:26,696 --> 00:25:29,157
My son is refusing to let her go.

370
00:26:23,336 --> 00:26:24,337
Hae-in.

371
00:28:16,866 --> 00:28:18,785
I'm left with only two valuable things

372
00:28:19,619 --> 00:28:21,579
in this life you've given me.

373
00:28:22,622 --> 00:28:24,416
The memories of loving others

374
00:28:25,041 --> 00:28:26,543
and being loved back.

375
00:28:27,544 --> 00:28:29,337
I can't let go of them.

376
00:28:31,756 --> 00:28:34,050
I won't ask you to save me.

377
00:28:34,134 --> 00:28:35,135
But please,

378
00:28:36,344 --> 00:28:37,721
let me cherish

379
00:28:38,221 --> 00:28:40,140
these memories until my last breath.

380
00:29:11,212 --> 00:29:12,046
Hae-in.

381
00:29:32,901 --> 00:29:35,445
Hae-in, I'm sorry.

382
00:29:36,321 --> 00:29:37,697
I'm sorry.

383
00:29:39,199 --> 00:29:40,909
Don't do this to me.

384
00:29:42,619 --> 00:29:45,330
Don't make me want to live.

385
00:29:54,672 --> 00:29:57,217
I won't be able to recognize you.

386
00:30:00,386 --> 00:30:02,680
I'll become a stranger.

387
00:30:12,982 --> 00:30:14,984
Even if that's the case,

388
00:30:16,778 --> 00:30:18,696
I'll be the first person you meet.

389
00:30:20,824 --> 00:30:23,284
Then you'll fall in love with me again.

390
00:30:24,118 --> 00:30:26,788
Your heart will race again
when I get drunk and act cute.

391
00:30:27,789 --> 00:30:29,833
We can love once again.

392
00:30:43,096 --> 00:30:44,347
I'll be by your side

393
00:30:45,390 --> 00:30:46,599
even if…

394
00:30:48,017 --> 00:30:49,644
you don't fall for me,

395
00:30:49,727 --> 00:30:50,979
ignore me,

396
00:30:52,605 --> 00:30:53,439
or…

397
00:30:54,566 --> 00:30:55,984
dislike me.

398
00:30:58,361 --> 00:30:59,863
I made a promise.

399
00:31:03,366 --> 00:31:04,993
That I'd stay by your side…

400
00:31:06,953 --> 00:31:08,454
even if you had debt…

401
00:31:10,623 --> 00:31:11,708
or something more.

402
00:31:13,501 --> 00:31:14,794
So…

403
00:31:16,421 --> 00:31:17,714
don't worry

404
00:31:18,715 --> 00:31:20,758
and just stay here, please.

405
00:31:21,759 --> 00:31:23,094
Don't pray

406
00:31:23,177 --> 00:31:24,929
about dying.

407
00:31:27,056 --> 00:31:28,308
I'm terrified…

408
00:31:31,728 --> 00:31:34,063
that it'll come true.

409
00:31:43,990 --> 00:31:45,491
Hae-in.

410
00:32:43,841 --> 00:32:45,468
I need to go to the toilet.

411
00:32:46,886 --> 00:32:47,804
Go eat first.

412
00:33:33,307 --> 00:33:34,308
What are you doing?

413
00:33:37,437 --> 00:33:38,438
What do you mean?

414
00:33:41,566 --> 00:33:44,027
You never drink coffee
on an empty stomach,

415
00:33:44,110 --> 00:33:45,862
but you're having espresso?

416
00:33:47,196 --> 00:33:49,532
Are you reading
that English newspaper to look smart

417
00:33:49,615 --> 00:33:53,369
while intentionally flexing
your forearm muscles?

418
00:33:59,751 --> 00:34:00,585
That's right.

419
00:34:10,053 --> 00:34:12,055
Yes, I'm doing this intentionally.

420
00:34:16,309 --> 00:34:17,143
Hold on.

421
00:34:17,935 --> 00:34:20,980
Are you acting freely
since we haven't registered our marriage?

422
00:34:21,814 --> 00:34:25,443
You're married,
so quit trying to impress others.

423
00:34:25,526 --> 00:34:28,029
Roll down your sleeves,
fasten the buttons,

424
00:34:28,112 --> 00:34:30,448
and have some scrambled eggs
with some ketchup.

425
00:34:37,246 --> 00:34:38,081
I don't want to.

426
00:34:39,248 --> 00:34:41,584
-Why not?
-I'm going to get under your skin.

427
00:34:42,877 --> 00:34:43,878
What?

428
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:47,381
You said I'd be a waste.

429
00:34:51,886 --> 00:34:53,387
You'd be the biggest waste.

430
00:34:59,769 --> 00:35:00,853
Did you

431
00:35:02,021 --> 00:35:03,147
hear that?

432
00:35:04,690 --> 00:35:07,068
I'm going to make it unbearable for you

433
00:35:07,944 --> 00:35:09,195
to leave me behind.

434
00:35:15,326 --> 00:35:16,786
I should have some fruit.

435
00:35:31,676 --> 00:35:34,178
He'd still be the biggest waste.

436
00:35:40,059 --> 00:35:41,936
The DNA test result is out.

437
00:35:42,019 --> 00:35:45,064
The victim's blood
was on the car seat and the murder weapon.

438
00:35:45,148 --> 00:35:46,774
And the prints on the weapon?

439
00:35:46,858 --> 00:35:48,609
Here it is. It's this guy.

440
00:35:57,034 --> 00:35:58,661
Roll down your sleeves and button them.

441
00:35:58,744 --> 00:36:01,873
You shouldn't show off
your arms like that.

442
00:36:01,956 --> 00:36:03,666
-It's my choice.
-Hey.

443
00:36:03,749 --> 00:36:04,750
Roll them down.

444
00:36:05,376 --> 00:36:07,003
-No.
-Do it.

445
00:36:07,086 --> 00:36:07,920
I don't want to.

446
00:36:23,186 --> 00:36:25,062
How's Ms. Hong's treatment going?

447
00:36:25,146 --> 00:36:26,606
-Will she be reinstated?
-Of course.

448
00:36:26,689 --> 00:36:29,150
Will she take charge once again?

449
00:36:29,233 --> 00:36:31,611
Well, I'm not sure about that.

450
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:34,614
We're all suffering here.

451
00:36:34,697 --> 00:36:37,074
You can tell if a company is going down

452
00:36:37,158 --> 00:36:38,910
based on the cafeteria and the pantry.

453
00:36:38,993 --> 00:36:42,079
It did shock me when they got rid
of the coffee machine.

454
00:36:42,163 --> 00:36:43,873
Did you go to the cafeteria today?

455
00:36:43,956 --> 00:36:46,250
They even stopped giving
Yakult as dessert.

456
00:36:48,085 --> 00:36:51,088
The company doesn't care
about our gut health anymore.

457
00:36:51,172 --> 00:36:55,760
I know our fates depend on our bosses,
but shouldn't we do something?

458
00:36:55,843 --> 00:36:58,262
I'm not sure

459
00:36:59,013 --> 00:37:01,224
if Secretary Kim feels the same way.

460
00:37:02,934 --> 00:37:03,976
-Why me?
-You played

461
00:37:04,060 --> 00:37:06,312
a key role in the current management.

462
00:37:06,395 --> 00:37:08,814
You're mistaken. I just ran a few errands.

463
00:37:08,898 --> 00:37:11,067
And you were rewarded.

464
00:37:11,609 --> 00:37:12,443
I was.

465
00:37:12,526 --> 00:37:14,570
-But it didn't feel good.
-Why not?

466
00:37:14,654 --> 00:37:18,032
Director Baek has been
awfully kind and forgiving.

467
00:37:18,115 --> 00:37:21,452
He paid for my sibling's college tuition,
so I couldn't be too happy.

468
00:37:21,535 --> 00:37:23,704
That's your guilt talking.

469
00:37:23,788 --> 00:37:25,957
Not all rewards are great.

470
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,166
You're getting a call.

471
00:37:28,542 --> 00:37:29,377
Hello?

472
00:37:30,127 --> 00:37:31,212
Yes, it's me.

473
00:37:31,295 --> 00:37:32,338
What? Where?

474
00:37:38,135 --> 00:37:41,013
Pyeon Seong-uk was found dead.

475
00:37:41,806 --> 00:37:42,807
He was murdered.

476
00:37:42,890 --> 00:37:43,724
Are you serious?

477
00:37:43,808 --> 00:37:45,893
The news broke out
when you left for Germany.

478
00:37:45,977 --> 00:37:47,103
I just found out too.

479
00:37:49,647 --> 00:37:50,940
All right.

480
00:37:55,778 --> 00:37:57,738
Sir, I tracked down the suspect.

481
00:37:57,822 --> 00:37:58,698
What?

482
00:37:58,781 --> 00:38:00,950
He fled to Frankfurt after the incident.

483
00:38:01,033 --> 00:38:02,076
I tracked down

484
00:38:02,159 --> 00:38:03,786
-his current location too.
-Okay.

485
00:38:03,869 --> 00:38:06,998
Let's request a warrant
and send it to the Foreign Affairs Bureau.

486
00:38:07,081 --> 00:38:08,833
It'll be a headache if he vanishes abroad.

487
00:38:08,916 --> 00:38:10,126
Yes, sir.

488
00:38:10,209 --> 00:38:11,335
Hey.

489
00:38:11,877 --> 00:38:13,129
This should be confidential.

490
00:38:13,212 --> 00:38:15,506
Don't let the media find out
before we catch him.

491
00:38:15,589 --> 00:38:16,882
Yes, sir. I'm aware.

492
00:38:20,928 --> 00:38:23,139
-I met with Da-hye.
-Sorry?

493
00:38:23,222 --> 00:38:24,682
You could've just sent me.

494
00:38:24,765 --> 00:38:26,225
I didn't know she was so dumb.

495
00:38:26,309 --> 00:38:27,768
I told you.

496
00:38:27,852 --> 00:38:30,187
-She fell for Soo-cheol.
-So I called Jun-ho.

497
00:38:30,271 --> 00:38:32,273
Why would you call that scumbag?

498
00:38:33,691 --> 00:38:35,609
So he can take care of her?

499
00:38:35,693 --> 00:38:38,070
I spared her out of pity,
and she's causing problems.

500
00:38:38,154 --> 00:38:39,655
I'll get rid of them one by one.

501
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:47,413
Did you send those men to Germany recently

502
00:38:47,496 --> 00:38:49,123
to take care of someone?

503
00:38:50,082 --> 00:38:51,417
They won't be coming back.

504
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:56,088
Wire them money when they call
and find a place for them to stay.

505
00:38:56,172 --> 00:38:57,048
Yes, ma'am.

506
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:16,025
Why won't they return?

507
00:39:16,108 --> 00:39:19,403
How serious is their crime
that they're not coming back?

508
00:39:23,532 --> 00:39:25,034
Hey, Ko Jeong-ja.

509
00:39:26,452 --> 00:39:28,954
Don't be naive.
You know what's going to happen.

510
00:39:33,667 --> 00:39:35,878
I think she's going to harm Hae-in.

511
00:39:52,645 --> 00:39:54,105
60,000,000,000 WON

512
00:39:57,525 --> 00:39:58,526
Get a grip.

513
00:39:58,609 --> 00:40:01,862
No one is better than you
at tolerating injustice.

514
00:40:04,198 --> 00:40:05,032
Yes.

515
00:40:06,117 --> 00:40:07,201
Just forget about it.

516
00:40:25,177 --> 00:40:26,011
Hello?

517
00:40:30,766 --> 00:40:31,600
Hello?

518
00:40:32,393 --> 00:40:33,686
It's me, Grace.

519
00:40:33,769 --> 00:40:35,521
Hello. What's this about?

520
00:40:35,604 --> 00:40:36,856
I'm just saying hello.

521
00:40:36,939 --> 00:40:38,232
Is everyone doing well?

522
00:40:39,942 --> 00:40:41,902
-Sorry?
-I guess they are.

523
00:40:41,986 --> 00:40:43,279
I'm glad then.

524
00:40:43,362 --> 00:40:46,365
Continue to stay safe until you return.

525
00:40:46,449 --> 00:40:47,575
Goodbye, then.

526
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,627
Hae…

527
00:41:40,836 --> 00:41:42,922
Hae-in…

528
00:41:43,005 --> 00:41:44,673
Hae-in.

529
00:41:46,550 --> 00:41:47,384
Hae-in.

530
00:41:53,933 --> 00:41:55,935
Hae-in!

531
00:41:59,355 --> 00:42:02,107
Hello? There's been a car accident.

532
00:42:02,191 --> 00:42:04,318
I think it was a hit-and-run.

533
00:42:04,401 --> 00:42:05,236
Hae-in…

534
00:42:06,862 --> 00:42:07,738
Hae-in!

535
00:42:08,989 --> 00:42:11,075
I reported it!

536
00:42:11,158 --> 00:42:14,119
Oh, my God. Step back!

537
00:42:14,203 --> 00:42:17,289
The car could explode! Get back!

538
00:42:19,750 --> 00:42:20,793
Hyun-woo!

539
00:42:41,564 --> 00:42:43,065
What's going on?

540
00:42:43,983 --> 00:42:45,568
Calm down. Okay?

541
00:42:45,651 --> 00:42:47,736
Did you get in a car crash? How?

542
00:42:50,698 --> 00:42:51,532
Even still…

543
00:42:52,157 --> 00:42:53,409
Are you crazy?

544
00:42:53,492 --> 00:42:56,745
How could you break the window
with your bare hand? Look at this!

545
00:42:58,956 --> 00:42:59,999
Look at your hand!

546
00:43:15,514 --> 00:43:16,932
I thought you were dead.

547
00:43:31,530 --> 00:43:32,573
I'm…

548
00:43:33,365 --> 00:43:34,199
I'm…

549
00:43:34,825 --> 00:43:35,909
I'm relieved.

550
00:43:44,585 --> 00:43:45,419
It's okay.

551
00:43:47,087 --> 00:43:48,088
It's okay.

552
00:43:50,132 --> 00:43:51,383
Everything's okay.

553
00:44:04,605 --> 00:44:07,024
EMERGENCY ROOM

554
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:10,569
Are you okay?

555
00:44:11,362 --> 00:44:12,446
It hurts.

556
00:44:15,616 --> 00:44:18,118
You shouldn't have acted like a lunatic.

557
00:44:18,786 --> 00:44:19,953
I really was one

558
00:44:20,746 --> 00:44:23,290
since I witnessed the crash.

559
00:44:23,791 --> 00:44:25,209
I thought you were in the car.

560
00:44:26,502 --> 00:44:28,379
When did you get out?

561
00:44:30,214 --> 00:44:32,007
I guess lady luck does exist.

562
00:44:45,396 --> 00:44:46,271
Look.

563
00:44:46,355 --> 00:44:47,898
I bought it again.

564
00:44:47,981 --> 00:44:50,484
It was still just as expensive.

565
00:44:50,567 --> 00:44:51,568
But this

566
00:44:52,820 --> 00:44:53,654
saved my life.

567
00:45:00,994 --> 00:45:02,913
Will you sob like that if I die?

568
00:45:02,996 --> 00:45:03,831
Of course.

569
00:45:07,084 --> 00:45:08,502
Then that won't do.

570
00:45:10,879 --> 00:45:12,005
What do you mean?

571
00:45:12,756 --> 00:45:15,426
You tug too much at my heartstrings.

572
00:45:15,509 --> 00:45:17,261
You make people want to hug you.

573
00:45:17,344 --> 00:45:20,264
You look sexy with your sleeves up,
you're cute when you're drunk,

574
00:45:20,347 --> 00:45:22,850
and you make others want to hug you
when you're crying.

575
00:45:23,684 --> 00:45:25,144
Women will be lining up.

576
00:45:25,811 --> 00:45:27,563
And I won't allow that.

577
00:45:27,646 --> 00:45:30,232
I'd be turning in my grave.

578
00:45:30,899 --> 00:45:32,192
What are you saying?

579
00:45:34,987 --> 00:45:36,196
I'll get the surgery.

580
00:45:42,995 --> 00:45:44,246
Do you mean that?

581
00:45:47,416 --> 00:45:50,252
I'm terrified because I don't know

582
00:45:50,335 --> 00:45:53,630
if I'll just lose my memory
or who I am entirely.

583
00:45:55,090 --> 00:45:56,842
But I don't want to lose you.

584
00:46:04,475 --> 00:46:06,560
I don't want to see you cry anymore.

585
00:46:06,643 --> 00:46:09,021
I persuaded you
into marrying me by promising

586
00:46:09,104 --> 00:46:11,023
that I'd never make you cry.

587
00:46:12,483 --> 00:46:14,276
I should start keeping my promise.

588
00:46:22,451 --> 00:46:23,285
Thank you.

589
00:46:23,911 --> 00:46:25,788
I understand how you must feel.

590
00:46:28,248 --> 00:46:29,583
You must be extremely anxious

591
00:46:30,584 --> 00:46:31,543
and terrified.

592
00:46:32,461 --> 00:46:34,421
But you will never

593
00:46:34,505 --> 00:46:36,173
lose yourself.

594
00:46:37,049 --> 00:46:38,467
I won't let that happen.

595
00:46:38,967 --> 00:46:40,135
I'll help you stay

596
00:46:41,178 --> 00:46:42,554
who you are.

597
00:46:43,764 --> 00:46:44,598
Okay.

598
00:46:45,432 --> 00:46:46,266
All right.

599
00:46:47,559 --> 00:46:48,393
I trust you.

600
00:46:54,233 --> 00:46:57,194
Gosh, Pinky. You eat so well.

601
00:46:57,277 --> 00:46:58,237
Is it tasty?

602
00:46:58,320 --> 00:46:59,822
-Let's talk.
-No thanks.

603
00:46:59,905 --> 00:47:00,989
What's with you?

604
00:47:01,073 --> 00:47:02,616
The building was always my turf.

605
00:47:02,699 --> 00:47:04,660
This could cause a rift between us.

606
00:47:06,578 --> 00:47:08,163
-I think I'm getting divorced.
-What?

607
00:47:08,872 --> 00:47:11,250
Are you tired
of living far from your family?

608
00:47:12,501 --> 00:47:13,585
Of course.

609
00:47:13,669 --> 00:47:16,922
I don't know when my husband
will get his doctorate.

610
00:47:17,714 --> 00:47:20,175
I sent my son abroad
to broaden his horizons.

611
00:47:22,052 --> 00:47:24,930
And I think he's too busy to miss me.

612
00:47:25,013 --> 00:47:26,223
Then go live with them.

613
00:47:26,306 --> 00:47:27,599
Then who'll be the breadwinner?

614
00:47:27,683 --> 00:47:29,226
I can't rely on Hyun-woo forever.

615
00:47:29,309 --> 00:47:30,686
So you'll get a divorce?

616
00:47:31,562 --> 00:47:32,896
-That's not why.
-Then?

617
00:47:34,398 --> 00:47:35,899
-I think he's having an affair.
-What?

618
00:47:35,983 --> 00:47:38,277
An American woman answered his phone.

619
00:47:38,360 --> 00:47:39,862
And it was late at night.

620
00:47:51,540 --> 00:47:54,710
Why would you give such a lousy reply?

621
00:47:56,795 --> 00:47:57,880
Beats me.

622
00:47:59,882 --> 00:48:02,134
I just blurted it out
the moment she talked.

623
00:48:02,968 --> 00:48:05,178
Jeez, he's really smart.

624
00:48:05,262 --> 00:48:08,640
He intentionally chose an American woman.

625
00:48:08,724 --> 00:48:12,728
He knew you barely spoke the language
and couldn't confront them.

626
00:48:12,811 --> 00:48:13,812
Gosh.

627
00:48:13,896 --> 00:48:16,315
It's true that I can't confront them

628
00:48:17,190 --> 00:48:19,151
or go there myself.

629
00:48:19,610 --> 00:48:20,444
HAIRSTYLIST AWARDS

630
00:48:21,403 --> 00:48:23,322
I have to remain here.

631
00:48:23,405 --> 00:48:25,407
So please help me.

632
00:48:25,490 --> 00:48:26,491
Goodness.

633
00:48:29,578 --> 00:48:30,579
Fine.

634
00:48:31,663 --> 00:48:33,040
You can have the building.

635
00:48:33,582 --> 00:48:34,499
It's all yours.

636
00:48:36,251 --> 00:48:37,127
Thanks.

637
00:48:40,213 --> 00:48:42,549
Gosh, don't cry.

638
00:48:42,633 --> 00:48:45,719
I'll give him an earful
when I see that scumbag.

639
00:48:45,802 --> 00:48:47,721
How could he date an American woman?

640
00:48:48,722 --> 00:48:49,890
Jeez.

641
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:53,185
Welcome.

642
00:48:53,268 --> 00:48:54,311
Hello.

643
00:48:54,394 --> 00:48:55,687
Where's Du-gwan?

644
00:48:55,771 --> 00:48:57,606
He's at the market.

645
00:48:57,689 --> 00:49:00,275
He seems busy these days,
so I said I'd take over his store.

646
00:49:00,359 --> 00:49:02,486
-I see. So you're part-timing?
-"Part-timing"?

647
00:49:03,195 --> 00:49:04,363
No.

648
00:49:04,446 --> 00:49:05,864
I'm experienced.

649
00:49:05,948 --> 00:49:08,158
I used to be the CEO
of a mart franchise in Seoul.

650
00:49:08,241 --> 00:49:10,702
-I see.
-This is like Unexpected Business.

651
00:49:10,786 --> 00:49:12,704
What is that?

652
00:49:12,788 --> 00:49:14,373
It's that variety show

653
00:49:14,456 --> 00:49:15,999
with Cha Tae-hyun and Zo In-sung.

654
00:49:16,083 --> 00:49:17,709
They manage a store.

655
00:49:17,793 --> 00:49:19,378
You're right.

656
00:49:21,964 --> 00:49:22,839
That's it!

657
00:49:22,923 --> 00:49:24,007
All right.

658
00:49:24,091 --> 00:49:25,175
SNOW CRAB RAMYEON
3,500 WON

659
00:49:25,258 --> 00:49:27,094
Goodness, look at this.

660
00:49:27,177 --> 00:49:29,137
This is a feast.

661
00:49:30,180 --> 00:49:31,056
Gosh.

662
00:49:31,139 --> 00:49:34,810
It wasn't easy
to get these snow crabs from Uljin.

663
00:49:34,893 --> 00:49:36,144
Express delivery was expensive.

664
00:49:36,228 --> 00:49:37,688
Shouldn't you charge more

665
00:49:37,771 --> 00:49:40,857
than the regular ramyeon price
of 3,500 won?

666
00:49:41,441 --> 00:49:43,402
I'm not trying to make a profit.

667
00:49:43,485 --> 00:49:44,361
Then what?

668
00:49:45,779 --> 00:49:48,740
Chapter One of my book,
The Neighborhood Business King,

669
00:49:48,824 --> 00:49:52,703
is "Ask Your Neighbors for Love,
Not Money."

670
00:49:52,786 --> 00:49:54,204
You wrote a book?

671
00:49:54,287 --> 00:49:56,289
I will, based on this experience.

672
00:49:58,208 --> 00:50:00,752
This looks amazing.

673
00:50:00,836 --> 00:50:02,337
-There's abalone inside too.
-Gosh!

674
00:50:02,421 --> 00:50:03,672
-Goodness.
-Abalone?

675
00:50:03,755 --> 00:50:05,674
-Hey.
-I heard the news.

676
00:50:05,757 --> 00:50:07,426
They're filming Unexpected Business here?

677
00:50:07,509 --> 00:50:08,677
Is In-sung here?

678
00:50:08,760 --> 00:50:10,178
No, he's not.

679
00:50:10,262 --> 00:50:11,513
But there's snow crab ramyeon.

680
00:50:11,596 --> 00:50:14,057
There's abalone too,
and it's only 3,500 won.

681
00:50:14,141 --> 00:50:15,600
-It's a bang for the buck.
-Right.

682
00:50:15,684 --> 00:50:17,477
I'd like a double portion.

683
00:50:17,561 --> 00:50:19,229
-Okay.
-Can I have a bite?

684
00:50:19,312 --> 00:50:20,480
Thanks.

685
00:50:25,318 --> 00:50:27,863
You know what? I'm going to invite
my mom and all the ladies.

686
00:50:27,946 --> 00:50:29,448
Should we tell our kids to come too?

687
00:50:29,531 --> 00:50:31,616
-Yes, we should.
-All right.

688
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:32,701
Look here, In-sung.

689
00:50:32,784 --> 00:50:34,161
Come on. I'm working.

690
00:50:36,079 --> 00:50:38,582
You're making me feel embarrassed.

691
00:50:48,842 --> 00:50:50,761
-Enjoy.
-Why, thank you.

692
00:50:50,844 --> 00:50:52,220
Goodness. I told you to rest.

693
00:50:53,138 --> 00:50:55,390
I know, but I just can't.

694
00:50:55,474 --> 00:50:57,309
What's going on?

695
00:50:57,392 --> 00:50:58,727
It's a huge hit.

696
00:50:58,810 --> 00:51:00,145
I didn't expect it either.

697
00:51:01,146 --> 00:51:02,147
Check this out.

698
00:51:02,230 --> 00:51:05,150
I've emptied out your ramyeon aisle.

699
00:51:05,233 --> 00:51:07,027
-I can see that.
-They all love it.

700
00:51:07,110 --> 00:51:09,446
Someone had three servings at once.

701
00:51:09,529 --> 00:51:11,364
Chun-sik's entire family came by

702
00:51:11,448 --> 00:51:14,201
and had their lunch and dinner's worth.

703
00:51:14,284 --> 00:51:16,369
Chun-sik, that bastard.

704
00:51:16,453 --> 00:51:17,662
-Sorry?
-Look.

705
00:51:17,746 --> 00:51:18,747
Listen to me.

706
00:51:19,372 --> 00:51:22,709
You won't be making a profit
considering the snow crabs, abalone,

707
00:51:22,793 --> 00:51:24,795
shrimp, and the delivery fee, you know?

708
00:51:24,878 --> 00:51:26,254
We're in debt.

709
00:51:26,338 --> 00:51:29,257
No, this is just a marketing strategy.

710
00:51:31,384 --> 00:51:33,261
I'm sorry for all the inconvenience,

711
00:51:33,345 --> 00:51:36,014
but I feel the most guilty
about leaving him behind.

712
00:51:36,098 --> 00:51:39,810
It feels like leaving
a bag of trash behind

713
00:51:39,893 --> 00:51:41,144
after a trip.

714
00:51:41,228 --> 00:51:43,146
He was warning me.

715
00:51:43,230 --> 00:51:44,981
We're not making a profit from ramyeon.

716
00:51:45,065 --> 00:51:48,235
Our goal is to make them
spend money on something more expensive.

717
00:51:48,318 --> 00:51:53,365
Ramyeon is
the most expensive food we have.

718
00:51:57,160 --> 00:51:58,161
I see.

719
00:52:05,001 --> 00:52:07,587
I totally overlooked that.

720
00:52:08,839 --> 00:52:10,257
So did you get fired?

721
00:52:11,550 --> 00:52:13,802
I took responsibility and resigned.

722
00:52:13,885 --> 00:52:17,347
Stop causing inconveniences
and go back to Seoul.

723
00:52:19,391 --> 00:52:20,225
No.

724
00:52:20,976 --> 00:52:24,604
I'm going to continue interacting
with the consumers here

725
00:52:24,688 --> 00:52:29,109
and find a way for farmers
and big marts to coexist.

726
00:52:37,742 --> 00:52:40,662
Did you think stealing my passport
would prevent me from coming to Korea?

727
00:52:40,745 --> 00:52:41,705
Where are you?

728
00:52:41,788 --> 00:52:45,041
Ms. Moh told me
that you're hiding in Hyun-woo's hometown.

729
00:52:45,125 --> 00:52:47,377
Should I go there right now? Should I?

730
00:52:47,460 --> 00:52:48,795
No, please don't do that.

731
00:52:49,588 --> 00:52:50,422
I'm sorry.

732
00:52:50,505 --> 00:52:51,715
If you want to save Soo-cheol,

733
00:52:51,798 --> 00:52:54,885
meet me at the address I sent
with everything you stole.

734
00:52:54,968 --> 00:52:56,219
I won't repeat myself.

735
00:53:00,182 --> 00:53:01,892
There's an amusement park nearby.

736
00:53:02,434 --> 00:53:03,935
Should we go there tomorrow?

737
00:53:05,061 --> 00:53:06,646
I'm down. I'll make gimbap.

738
00:53:07,314 --> 00:53:09,357
Geon-u, we're going to an amusement park!

739
00:53:09,441 --> 00:53:10,400
An amusement park!

740
00:53:14,821 --> 00:53:15,947
Aren't you fascinated?

741
00:53:16,031 --> 00:53:16,865
What is this?

742
00:53:16,948 --> 00:53:19,034
Where's Mommy?

743
00:53:19,117 --> 00:53:20,202
There she is.

744
00:53:20,285 --> 00:53:21,286
Hi, Mommy.

745
00:53:29,961 --> 00:53:30,879
Geon-u, Mommy's here!

746
00:53:32,380 --> 00:53:34,507
Let's eat.

747
00:53:35,217 --> 00:53:37,010
-How tasty.
-How tasty.

748
00:53:39,179 --> 00:53:40,180
-Is it good?
-It's good.

749
00:53:42,641 --> 00:53:44,351
Geon-u, look at me.

750
00:53:44,976 --> 00:53:47,062
Good boy. Well done.

751
00:53:47,145 --> 00:53:47,979
Geon-u.

752
00:53:48,605 --> 00:53:49,606
Good boy.

753
00:53:52,317 --> 00:53:53,610
I'm tired.

754
00:53:54,277 --> 00:53:56,613
-Can you buy me some coffee?
-Coffee?

755
00:53:56,696 --> 00:53:58,615
Wait here. I'll get some.

756
00:54:01,284 --> 00:54:02,535
It's chilly, right?

757
00:54:08,583 --> 00:54:10,293
Okay. Your hand.

758
00:54:34,776 --> 00:54:36,403
-I'll be back soon.
-Okay.

759
00:55:04,389 --> 00:55:05,223
I'm sorry.

760
00:55:22,282 --> 00:55:23,783
Did she go to the toilet?

761
00:55:50,143 --> 00:55:51,394
Da-hye…

762
00:55:51,895 --> 00:55:52,729
Da-hye!

763
00:55:55,565 --> 00:55:56,399
Da-hye!

764
00:55:58,193 --> 00:55:59,027
Da…

765
00:56:00,403 --> 00:56:02,447
Da-hye!

766
00:56:04,032 --> 00:56:04,991
Da-hye!

767
00:56:05,700 --> 00:56:07,243
Da-hye…

768
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:10,538
Da-hye…

769
00:56:11,039 --> 00:56:13,625
Da-hye…

770
00:56:15,960 --> 00:56:19,297
Why did you leave me again?

771
00:56:25,595 --> 00:56:27,180
This is a public announcement.

772
00:56:27,263 --> 00:56:31,976
Mr. Hong Soo-cheol, 31,
is looking for his wife.

773
00:56:32,060 --> 00:56:34,771
Please come to the Lost Children Center…

774
00:56:34,854 --> 00:56:37,941
-What? But he's an adult.
-…as soon as you hear this.

775
00:56:38,024 --> 00:56:39,401
Once again--

776
00:56:39,484 --> 00:56:40,485
Da-hye.

777
00:56:41,903 --> 00:56:42,904
Please, don't go.

778
00:56:43,988 --> 00:56:44,823
I…

779
00:56:45,615 --> 00:56:47,409
I'll do better.

780
00:56:50,078 --> 00:56:52,372
I promise.

781
00:56:53,248 --> 00:56:54,582
So please don't leave.

782
00:56:55,583 --> 00:56:58,294
What? Did his wife
abandon him here and run away?

783
00:56:58,378 --> 00:57:00,713
No way. He was abandoned.

784
00:57:00,797 --> 00:57:04,300
He must be a loser
for her to leave him here.

785
00:57:04,384 --> 00:57:05,427
He's not a loser.

786
00:57:06,511 --> 00:57:07,554
Sorry?

787
00:57:07,637 --> 00:57:09,097
He's not a loser.

788
00:57:09,931 --> 00:57:11,474
My husband

789
00:57:11,558 --> 00:57:13,476
is the most amazing man ever.

790
00:57:22,819 --> 00:57:24,612
It's okay. Let's go.

791
00:57:45,467 --> 00:57:47,427
Where did you go after leaving me?

792
00:57:48,178 --> 00:57:49,846
What are you doing here?

793
00:58:01,399 --> 00:58:03,359
You're making it hard for me to leave.

794
00:58:05,862 --> 00:58:07,530
Why are you doing this?

795
01:00:23,249 --> 01:00:24,626
It's my last night here.

796
01:00:25,251 --> 01:00:26,836
Don't give it any meaning.

797
01:00:26,919 --> 01:00:29,505
You'll always be yourself.

798
01:00:32,091 --> 01:00:33,384
Nevertheless,

799
01:00:34,052 --> 01:00:35,136
this is your chance.

800
01:00:35,678 --> 01:00:37,263
-For what?
-To come clean.

801
01:00:38,348 --> 01:00:40,308
I'll forget everything after the surgery.

802
01:00:40,933 --> 01:00:42,143
So?

803
01:00:44,062 --> 01:00:45,813
Complaints you had.

804
01:00:46,356 --> 01:00:47,899
Times when you felt hurt.

805
01:00:47,982 --> 01:00:49,609
Things you couldn't tell me.

806
01:00:49,692 --> 01:00:50,693
Stuff like that.

807
01:00:52,862 --> 01:00:54,364
You can be honest with me now.

808
01:00:59,202 --> 01:01:00,078
Forget it.

809
01:01:00,953 --> 01:01:04,332
I've fallen for that one too many times.

810
01:01:05,416 --> 01:01:06,501
Come on.

811
01:01:07,085 --> 01:01:08,544
I'll forget them anyway.

812
01:01:15,426 --> 01:01:16,260
Forget it.

813
01:01:20,598 --> 01:01:21,474
So…

814
01:01:22,558 --> 01:01:24,519
you do have some things.

815
01:01:27,355 --> 01:01:28,856
Don't try to sound me out.

816
01:01:33,277 --> 01:01:34,946
What do you have to lose?

817
01:01:35,029 --> 01:01:37,865
I'll be getting surgery soon,
so what's stopping you?

818
01:01:38,741 --> 01:01:39,575
Tell me.

819
01:01:41,703 --> 01:01:42,537
What?

820
01:01:43,621 --> 01:01:45,707
-Nothing?
-I'm trying to pick.

821
01:01:49,377 --> 01:01:50,795
There must be a lot.

822
01:01:50,878 --> 01:01:51,963
Not really.

823
01:02:00,972 --> 01:02:02,265
I'm only saying this

824
01:02:02,849 --> 01:02:04,559
because you told me to.

825
01:02:06,644 --> 01:02:08,563
You tend to change

826
01:02:09,230 --> 01:02:10,148
your mind often.

827
01:02:10,231 --> 01:02:11,607
What do you mean?

828
01:02:12,024 --> 01:02:13,443
I'll give you an example.

829
01:02:13,985 --> 01:02:16,487
You wanted me to remember our anniversary,

830
01:02:16,571 --> 01:02:17,739
so I prepared a surprise.

831
01:02:17,822 --> 01:02:20,366
Then you got mad about it,

832
01:02:20,450 --> 01:02:22,577
but you also got mad
when I didn't prepare anything.

833
01:02:22,660 --> 01:02:24,829
Everything in moderation.

834
01:02:24,912 --> 01:02:26,748
But that's your standard.

835
01:02:26,831 --> 01:02:30,168
I don't know what you're thinking,
so how would I know?

836
01:02:30,251 --> 01:02:32,628
-That's--
-Also, I'd like you to hear me out

837
01:02:32,712 --> 01:02:35,089
without getting mad when I talk to you.

838
01:02:35,173 --> 01:02:36,841
I'm good at that.

839
01:02:36,924 --> 01:02:37,967
You're mad even now.

840
01:02:39,886 --> 01:02:41,345
No, I'm listening attentively.

841
01:02:41,429 --> 01:02:43,055
I always frown when I listen.

842
01:02:43,139 --> 01:02:44,140
Also…

843
01:02:44,223 --> 01:02:45,725
You have a whole list.

844
01:02:45,808 --> 01:02:46,976
I love you.

845
01:02:52,815 --> 01:02:54,609
-What?
-I said I love you.

846
01:02:57,945 --> 01:03:00,615
You told me to say things
that I couldn't say before.

847
01:03:04,202 --> 01:03:05,161
I did say that.

848
01:03:06,621 --> 01:03:08,790
Keep talking. Say what's on your mind.

849
01:03:09,373 --> 01:03:10,249
Keep going.

850
01:03:16,088 --> 01:03:17,256
Thank you for making

851
01:03:18,257 --> 01:03:19,675
this hard decision.

852
01:03:20,802 --> 01:03:23,304
Don't get sick

853
01:03:23,387 --> 01:03:24,597
or hurt anymore.

854
01:03:25,264 --> 01:03:27,308
Stay by my side forever.

855
01:03:31,604 --> 01:03:33,981
Let's go on trips.

856
01:03:34,774 --> 01:03:35,733
Let's take walks.

857
01:03:36,359 --> 01:03:37,485
Let's work out.

858
01:03:37,568 --> 01:03:39,195
Let's argue and make up.

859
01:03:40,112 --> 01:03:42,240
Let's do ordinary things

860
01:03:43,157 --> 01:03:44,367
and grow old together.

861
01:03:50,206 --> 01:03:51,332
This is so unfair.

862
01:03:52,625 --> 01:03:54,961
I'll forget all these sweet words too.

863
01:03:56,629 --> 01:03:57,463
It's okay.

864
01:03:58,089 --> 01:03:59,215
I'll say them again.

865
01:03:59,298 --> 01:04:00,508
I'll say them every day.

866
01:04:04,303 --> 01:04:05,137
Hold on.

867
01:04:16,232 --> 01:04:17,066
Well…

868
01:04:18,192 --> 01:04:21,195
I wrote down everything I could think of

869
01:04:22,071 --> 01:04:23,239
about myself,

870
01:04:23,781 --> 01:04:26,701
you, and the life I've lived.

871
01:04:27,702 --> 01:04:29,120
I hope this will guide me

872
01:04:29,829 --> 01:04:31,497
in my next life.

873
01:04:32,748 --> 01:04:35,084
But I'll forget that I even have this.

874
01:04:35,626 --> 01:04:37,461
So keep it

875
01:04:38,087 --> 01:04:39,171
and give it to me.

876
01:04:43,384 --> 01:04:44,218
By the way,

877
01:04:44,844 --> 01:04:46,304
when did you write this?

878
01:04:46,971 --> 01:04:49,223
-Don't read it now.
-Okay.

879
01:04:49,307 --> 01:04:50,975
You can read it

880
01:04:51,851 --> 01:04:54,395
while you wait for me to wake up

881
01:04:55,271 --> 01:04:56,105
after the surgery.

882
01:04:58,399 --> 01:04:59,358
Okay.

883
01:04:59,442 --> 01:05:02,361
Don't change anything.
Don't make yourself sound better.

884
01:05:03,529 --> 01:05:04,363
All right.

885
01:05:08,034 --> 01:05:09,410
Come here.

886
01:05:52,495 --> 01:05:53,704
Hold on.

887
01:05:53,788 --> 01:05:56,958
Was the surgery at 10:00 a.m. in Germany?

888
01:05:58,376 --> 01:06:00,211
It's in ten minutes. Goodness.

889
01:06:00,878 --> 01:06:02,797
She'll be fine. Don't worry.

890
01:06:03,965 --> 01:06:05,841
Okay. Stop shaking your leg.

891
01:06:05,925 --> 01:06:06,759
Okay.

892
01:06:11,806 --> 01:06:12,640
Honey.

893
01:06:13,849 --> 01:06:15,267
Paengsun…

894
01:06:16,018 --> 01:06:17,436
-is alive.
-What?

895
01:06:18,229 --> 01:06:20,356
Really? The snail with no shell?

896
01:06:20,439 --> 01:06:21,941
Wasn't she dying?

897
01:06:23,484 --> 01:06:24,443
It's a miracle.

898
01:06:25,820 --> 01:06:26,821
It is.

899
01:06:28,948 --> 01:06:31,200
Gosh, Seon-hwa. This is a good sign.

900
01:06:33,077 --> 01:06:33,911
Do you think so?

901
01:06:33,995 --> 01:06:34,829
Yes.

902
01:06:35,496 --> 01:06:36,330
Of course.

903
01:06:37,999 --> 01:06:40,126
Hae-in's surgery will go well.

904
01:06:51,470 --> 01:06:52,805
Wait.

905
01:06:58,269 --> 01:06:59,854
You won't go anywhere, right?

906
01:07:00,896 --> 01:07:01,981
Of course not.

907
01:07:02,064 --> 01:07:04,692
You need to be by my side
when I open my eyes.

908
01:07:05,568 --> 01:07:06,736
It's like imprinting.

909
01:07:07,361 --> 01:07:10,239
I'm going to be
like a newly hatched duckling.

910
01:07:10,322 --> 01:07:12,033
I'll trust whomever I see first.

911
01:07:14,785 --> 01:07:15,786
Don't worry.

912
01:07:16,537 --> 01:07:19,540
I'll stay by your side
from the moment you open your eyes

913
01:07:20,166 --> 01:07:21,375
until you get sick of me.

914
01:07:21,459 --> 01:07:25,921
What if I don't remember anything
or recognize you?

915
01:07:26,714 --> 01:07:28,841
What if I mistreat you?

916
01:07:32,178 --> 01:07:34,263
It won't be my first rodeo.

917
01:07:36,015 --> 01:07:38,184
That won't matter at all.

918
01:07:38,267 --> 01:07:40,311
Just get the surgery

919
01:07:41,562 --> 01:07:42,396
and come back.

920
01:07:44,440 --> 01:07:46,817
Make sure you come back.

921
01:07:46,901 --> 01:07:48,194
I'll be back.

922
01:07:49,320 --> 01:07:50,529
Please take care of me

923
01:07:51,572 --> 01:07:52,656
when I return.

924
01:07:55,951 --> 01:07:57,119
I'll be back.

925
01:09:25,332 --> 01:09:26,542
HAE-IN HONG, IN SURGERY

926
01:09:26,625 --> 01:09:27,793
IN RECOVERY

927
01:09:40,848 --> 01:09:41,849
Mr. Baek Hyun-woo?

928
01:09:45,978 --> 01:09:46,937
Who are you?

929
01:09:47,563 --> 01:09:50,441
I'm Detective Kang Min-wook
from the German police force.

930
01:09:50,983 --> 01:09:52,401
What is this about?

931
01:09:52,484 --> 01:09:55,154
You're under arrest
for the murder of Mr. Pyeon Seong-uk.

932
01:09:56,947 --> 01:09:58,991
What do you mean? I'm a murder suspect?

933
01:09:59,074 --> 01:10:01,911
You have the right to remain silent
and hire an attorney.

934
01:10:01,994 --> 01:10:05,122
You can also file a complaint
if you think this arrest is unjust.

935
01:10:07,124 --> 01:10:08,000
Wait.

936
01:10:08,083 --> 01:10:09,877
This is a misunderstanding.

937
01:10:09,960 --> 01:10:10,920
Give me some time.

938
01:10:11,003 --> 01:10:12,338
We can talk at the station.

939
01:10:12,421 --> 01:10:13,255
Let's go.

940
01:10:15,507 --> 01:10:16,759
Wait!

941
01:10:16,842 --> 01:10:18,677
My wife is in surgery.

942
01:10:18,761 --> 01:10:20,304
I need to be there when she wakes up.

943
01:10:20,387 --> 01:10:22,181
Give me just 30 minutes.

944
01:10:22,264 --> 01:10:24,350
I promised to be there!

945
01:10:24,433 --> 01:10:26,060
I have to be there!

946
01:10:38,656 --> 01:10:40,032
Don't worry.

947
01:10:40,616 --> 01:10:42,534
I'll be her guardian.

948
01:10:43,160 --> 01:10:44,161
Was this your scheme?

949
01:10:45,204 --> 01:10:46,538
What scheme?

950
01:10:46,622 --> 01:10:47,498
I'm just protecting

951
01:10:48,666 --> 01:10:50,542
my woman from a criminal.

952
01:11:01,929 --> 01:11:02,763
Hae…

953
01:11:04,223 --> 01:11:05,099
Hae-in.

954
01:11:05,182 --> 01:11:07,434
Hae-in!

955
01:11:07,977 --> 01:11:08,978
Hae-in.

956
01:11:09,061 --> 01:11:11,021
Hae-in!

957
01:11:13,190 --> 01:11:15,651
Hae-in!

958
01:11:18,070 --> 01:11:19,238
Hae…

959
01:11:21,365 --> 01:11:22,324
Hae-in.

960
01:11:27,913 --> 01:11:28,789
Hae-in.

961
01:11:33,294 --> 01:11:36,547
Baek, the former director
of Queens' Legal Team,

962
01:11:36,630 --> 01:11:37,881
-was arrested in Frankfurt
-Mom.

963
01:11:37,965 --> 01:11:40,426
as the key suspect
in the reservoir murder that occurred

964
01:11:40,509 --> 01:11:43,012
in Sambang, Yeongjin-gun,
Gyeonggi Province last month.

965
01:11:43,095 --> 01:11:46,640
The police joined forces
with Interpol to arrest him

966
01:11:46,724 --> 01:11:48,225
and plan to request an arrest warrant

967
01:11:48,309 --> 01:11:50,352
for murder as soon
as he is brought to Korea.

968
01:11:50,436 --> 01:11:55,107
Wait. If Hyun-woo was arrested,
who is with Hae-in right now?

969
01:11:55,190 --> 01:11:56,567
What?

970
01:12:00,029 --> 01:12:02,239
Where's the number he gave us?

971
01:12:03,282 --> 01:12:04,158
Hold on.

972
01:12:04,950 --> 01:12:06,577
Beom-jun, here.

973
01:12:06,660 --> 01:12:07,578
GERMAN HOSPITAL

974
01:12:08,787 --> 01:12:09,747
Here it is.

975
01:12:17,046 --> 01:12:19,298
The hospital told me that you called.

976
01:12:20,049 --> 01:12:21,675
Don't worry. I'm by her side.

977
01:12:22,343 --> 01:12:23,761
The surgery went well,

978
01:12:23,844 --> 01:12:25,554
and she'll recover soon.

979
01:12:25,637 --> 01:12:27,306
We'll be there soon.

980
01:12:28,015 --> 01:12:28,891
Right.

981
01:12:29,558 --> 01:12:31,226
-I don't think so.
-What?

982
01:12:32,394 --> 01:12:33,228
What do you mean?

983
01:12:33,312 --> 01:12:35,147
I guess you haven't heard.

984
01:12:35,230 --> 01:12:37,691
I wanted to wait out of respect

985
01:12:37,775 --> 01:12:39,860
until Chairman Hong's funeral ended.

986
01:12:39,943 --> 01:12:41,570
But I couldn't turn a blind eye

987
01:12:41,653 --> 01:12:44,323
to your embezzlement and malpractice.

988
01:12:44,406 --> 01:12:46,492
The prosecution will begin
their investigation soon,

989
01:12:46,575 --> 01:12:48,285
so you won't be able to fly out.

990
01:12:48,369 --> 01:12:49,203
You bastard!

991
01:12:49,286 --> 01:12:51,580
I'll take care of Hae-in
and return to Korea.

992
01:12:51,663 --> 01:12:52,498
So…

993
01:12:54,917 --> 01:12:56,126
leave her to me.

994
01:13:07,846 --> 01:13:09,306
It's actually more

995
01:13:09,390 --> 01:13:10,391
of a request.

996
01:13:12,935 --> 01:13:15,354
A divorce withdrawal.

997
01:13:22,194 --> 01:13:23,987
That's a good date. October 31.

998
01:13:35,040 --> 01:13:36,166
Since the universe

999
01:13:36,917 --> 01:13:38,419
is on our side…

1000
01:13:38,502 --> 01:13:39,336
Will you…

1001
01:13:41,964 --> 01:13:42,840
marry me?

1002
01:13:53,851 --> 01:13:56,895
You'll be by my side?

1003
01:13:56,979 --> 01:13:57,855
Yes.

1004
01:13:59,022 --> 01:14:00,065
I'll be there

1005
01:14:00,899 --> 01:14:01,733
for you.

1006
01:14:08,031 --> 01:14:09,658
Dear Hae-in from the future.

1007
01:14:09,741 --> 01:14:11,660
I won't ask how you're doing since I know

1008
01:14:11,743 --> 01:14:12,870
you'll be doing fine.

1009
01:14:12,953 --> 01:14:15,497
You'll be just as pretty, healthy,

1010
01:14:15,581 --> 01:14:17,583
and the most successful.

1011
01:14:18,333 --> 01:14:19,209
With Hyun-woo

1012
01:14:20,210 --> 01:14:21,462
by your side, of course.

1013
01:15:12,387 --> 01:15:13,514
Are you finally awake?

1014
01:15:20,270 --> 01:15:22,564
Don't. You'll exhaust yourself.
Let me talk.

1015
01:15:24,650 --> 01:15:27,653
You're probably confused
and don't know who you are.

1016
01:15:27,736 --> 01:15:28,570
It's normal.

1017
01:15:29,112 --> 01:15:31,907
You just woke up from a major surgery.

1018
01:15:31,990 --> 01:15:35,202
A tumor was removed from your brain.

1019
01:15:35,827 --> 01:15:37,454
That's why you can't remember.

1020
01:15:38,038 --> 01:15:40,374
You asked me for a favor
before the surgery.

1021
01:15:40,457 --> 01:15:43,001
You asked me to be here when you woke up.

1022
01:15:43,085 --> 01:15:45,712
That's why I stayed here the entire time.

1023
01:15:48,674 --> 01:15:49,508
Baek Hyun-woo?

1024
01:16:32,634 --> 01:16:33,468
What is it?

1025
01:16:34,678 --> 01:16:36,138
Do you remember that name?

1026
01:16:36,221 --> 01:16:38,015
That's the only name I remember.

1027
01:16:40,809 --> 01:16:41,935
I'm not him.

1028
01:16:44,688 --> 01:16:46,148
You're Hong Hae-in.

1029
01:16:46,231 --> 01:16:47,649
I'm Yoon Eun-sung.

1030
01:16:51,361 --> 01:16:53,530
We started dating in college.

1031
01:16:53,614 --> 01:16:56,325
We had parted ways,
but we still love each other.

1032
01:16:58,118 --> 01:16:59,494
Baek Hyun-woo

1033
01:16:59,578 --> 01:17:00,871
is your ex-husband.

1034
01:17:01,747 --> 01:17:02,581
I was

1035
01:17:03,832 --> 01:17:04,916
married?

1036
01:17:06,752 --> 01:17:09,713
I didn't want to alarm you
when you've just woken up,

1037
01:17:09,796 --> 01:17:12,466
but he had completely deceived you.

1038
01:17:12,549 --> 01:17:13,967
That's why you divorced him.

1039
01:17:14,635 --> 01:17:16,219
I got a divorce?

1040
01:17:17,763 --> 01:17:20,390
He had stalked you until recently,

1041
01:17:20,474 --> 01:17:23,935
but he's been arrested
by Interpol as a murder suspect.

1042
01:17:25,687 --> 01:17:27,606
You must be startled. I'm sorry.

1043
01:17:28,440 --> 01:17:31,318
You probably remember his name

1044
01:17:31,401 --> 01:17:33,695
because of how much you suffered.

1045
01:17:34,821 --> 01:17:35,822
That's probably why.

1046
01:17:37,491 --> 01:17:40,160
Don't think about anything
and just rest up.

1047
01:17:40,243 --> 01:17:41,787
I'll bring the doctor.

1048
01:18:27,791 --> 01:18:29,876
I didn't think I'd ever see winter again

1049
01:18:29,960 --> 01:18:32,796
let alone the first snow.

1050
01:18:32,879 --> 01:18:34,673
But it's possible now.

1051
01:18:35,257 --> 01:18:36,091
Of course.

1052
01:18:37,217 --> 01:18:40,721
And it'll come true
if the color still remains by then.

1053
01:18:42,681 --> 01:18:43,682
What will come true?

1054
01:18:44,683 --> 01:18:45,767
My first love.

1055
01:19:01,366 --> 01:19:03,118
She must be awake by now.

1056
01:20:01,176 --> 01:20:02,219
It's snowing.

1057
01:20:16,691 --> 01:20:17,859
Is this the first snow?

1058
01:20:49,975 --> 01:20:50,976
What's wrong with me?

1059
01:20:52,477 --> 01:20:53,478
What?

1060
01:21:05,365 --> 01:21:06,741
It's so painful.

1061
01:21:51,494 --> 01:21:55,498
You used to tell me about those days
you were in law school.

1062
01:21:57,876 --> 01:21:58,919
Yeah?

1063
01:21:59,002 --> 01:22:01,338
You always bragged about your good memory.

1064
01:22:02,005 --> 01:22:03,006
And?

1065
01:22:03,965 --> 01:22:06,593
What was your secret to memorizing well?

1066
01:22:08,261 --> 01:22:09,387
I'm not sure.

1067
01:22:10,055 --> 01:22:11,848
I was able to easily remember

1068
01:22:12,849 --> 01:22:15,185
anything I looked at.

1069
01:22:16,019 --> 01:22:17,145
I'm serious.

1070
01:22:18,396 --> 01:22:21,066
Did you gobble up
the pages after memorizing them?

1071
01:22:22,984 --> 01:22:23,818
I'm not a goat.

1072
01:22:25,403 --> 01:22:26,404
Well…

1073
01:22:27,280 --> 01:22:28,907
I couldn't memorize everything.

1074
01:22:29,908 --> 01:22:31,660
So I repeatedly mumbled

1075
01:22:32,243 --> 01:22:34,955
the important parts.

1076
01:22:35,038 --> 01:22:36,247
Then I could remember

1077
01:22:37,290 --> 01:22:38,667
my voice during the test.

1078
01:22:38,750 --> 01:22:40,210
My subconscious remembered it.

1079
01:22:43,296 --> 01:22:44,297
Why do you ask?

1080
01:22:46,341 --> 01:22:47,175
No reason.

1081
01:22:51,221 --> 01:22:52,222
Go to bed.

1082
01:23:33,638 --> 01:23:34,764
Baek Hyun-woo.

1083
01:23:37,392 --> 01:23:38,727
Baek Hyun-woo.

1084
01:23:40,353 --> 01:23:41,646
Baek Hyun-woo.

1085
01:23:45,442 --> 01:23:46,443
Baek Hyun-woo.

1086
01:23:48,820 --> 01:23:50,238
Baek Hyun-woo.

1087
01:23:50,321 --> 01:23:52,365
Don't forget that name.

1088
01:23:55,869 --> 01:23:57,037
Baek Hyun-woo.

1089
01:24:01,249 --> 01:24:02,542
Baek Hyun-woo.

1090
01:24:04,335 --> 01:24:05,545
Baek Hyun-woo.

1091
01:24:14,304 --> 01:24:17,140
QUEEN OF TEARS

1092
01:24:47,712 --> 01:24:49,214
I was very worried.

1093
01:24:49,923 --> 01:24:52,425
I'm going to keep you safe.

1094
01:24:53,301 --> 01:24:55,720
I must've lived a lonely life.

1095
01:24:55,804 --> 01:24:58,264
They followed Hae-in to Germany
and kept me updated.

1096
01:24:58,348 --> 01:25:00,725
Please check the bus dashcams
around the time of the murder.

1097
01:25:00,809 --> 01:25:02,602
-Exactly!
-I'll get out no matter what.

1098
01:25:02,685 --> 01:25:03,853
Let Da-hye go!

1099
01:25:04,479 --> 01:25:07,816
This will prove that Eun-sung and his men
conducted a two-trillion investment fraud.

1100
01:25:07,899 --> 01:25:10,360
My heart is racing.

1101
01:25:10,485 --> 01:25:11,986
He is the person

1102
01:25:12,070 --> 01:25:14,030
-I want to remember forever.
-Hae-in!

1103
01:25:14,114 --> 01:25:15,156
We will meet again.

1104
01:25:15,240 --> 01:25:17,784
Because I won't give up.
I'll stay by your side.

1105
